  Move the package to crypto herd fully.

*pcsc-perl-1.4.11 (06 Dec 2010)

  06 Dec 2010; Diego E. Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  -pcsc-perl-1.4.7.ebuild, -pcsc-perl-1.4.9.ebuild, pcsc-perl-1.4.10.ebuild,
  +pcsc-perl-1.4.11.ebuild:
  Version bump to work with pcsc-lite 1.6.5; tweak dependencies for previous
  verison. Remove older versions.

*pcsc-perl-1.4.10 (08 Oct 2010)

  08 Oct 2010; Diego E. Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  pcsc-perl-1.4.9.ebuild, +pcsc-perl-1.4.10.ebuild:
  Version bump for pcsc-perl to build with pcsc 1.6.4; tweak dependencies on
  1.4.9 to require a previous version.

*pcsc-perl-1.4.9 (26 Jul 2010)

  26 Jul 2010; Steve Arnold <nerdboy@gentoo.org> pcsc-perl-1.4.7.ebuild,
  +pcsc-perl-1.4.9.ebuild:
  Updated to latest upstream to match new pcsc-lite package (fixes bug 
  326343).

  07 Feb 2010; Torsten Veller <tove@gentoo.org> pcsc-perl-1.4.7.ebuild:
  Drop ~mips (#142036)

*pcsc-perl-1.4.7 (11 Jan 2009)

  11 Jan 2009; Steve Arnold <nerdboy@gentoo.org> +metadata.xml,
  +pcsc-perl-1.4.7.ebuild:
  New ebuild for pcsc-perl. Ebuild written by me. Very handy for setting 
  up and using the PC/SC smartcard tools that go with the daemon package.  
  Tested with a USB smartcard reader (Axalto Reflex USB v3).  The older 
  reader I tried (mentioned on several forum posts) won't work without 
  a firmware update.
